Introduction.S:
In more recent times, two methods have been chiefly used 
    to locate the cells of origin of the spinothalamic tract: 
    electrophysiology, using antidromic activation with stimulating 
    electrodes in the brain and recording electrodes in the spinal cord 
    (Dilly et al., '68; Trevino et al., '72, '73; 
    AlbeFessard et al., '74a,b; and Giesler et al., '76); and 
    retrograde labelling with horseradish peroxidase (HRP) (Carstens 
    and Trevino, '78a,b; Giesler et al., '78, '79a; 
    Willis et al., '79; Granum and Webster, '81, '82; 
    Granum, '83).

